{
  "stem": "21626.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But back in our-- when we-- when we moved to our Welsh haven, and we had this beautiful hotel with a boating lake and a bit of the local river running through the grounds, and-- and a lovely new teacher, Miss Mackenzie, who was a Scottish lady, supplied, of course, by courtesy of the British Council, who introduced us to hockey and selected me as the captain.",
      "word_count": 67
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "You know, life went on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And-- and life had to go on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And you had to come to terms with living a happy life of a teenager and being at the same time consumed with fear and almost guilt because you were able to live this happy life.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the time went on so quickly and so pleasantly, holidays spent with my foster family or with my sister, and always the term time to look forward to.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Because it was-- it was like a home to me then.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But as time went and 1945 came-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] --then one began to be very nervous and very impatient.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "You know, once the British forces invaded France and started marching across Europe, we waited so impatiently for any news.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I wrote, and wrote, and wrote in my diary.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And it was so difficult to concentrate on studies and on any other things.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And then the news finally came.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I was the first child of the school to hear that mother had survived.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] My sister had a telegram from friends in Stockholm who wrote to say that both mother and father had survived-- congratulations-- and a letter following.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And everybody in the school was so happy for me, so thrilled for me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I couldn't believe my luck.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
